and it tastes horrible.

00:10.711 --> 00:12.713
That is a box
of stuffing mix.

00:15.749 --> 00:17.451
All right,
if this isn't cereal,

00:17.551 --> 00:20.321
then why did it come
with this cool prize I got?

00:20.421 --> 00:23.257
That is a bag of seasoning.

00:24.725 --> 00:26.727
Hey, guys.
There's no chance

00:26.827 --> 00:29.029
my mother's already come
and gone already, is there?

00:29.130 --> 00:30.464
No. She called to say

00:30.564 --> 00:31.732
that her hair appointment's
running long.

00:31.832 --> 00:34.702
Oh. How long
could it take?

00:34.802 --> 00:36.070
Somebody just holds her
by the ankles

00:37.037 --> 00:38.606
and dips her head into
a cotton candy machine.

00:38.706 --> 00:41.275
I love Bobbi.

00:41.375 --> 00:43.711
She's the kind of elderly
person you see on the street

00:43.811 --> 00:46.080
that you don't want
to knock down.

00:48.649 --> 00:51.051
Maybe you don't.
Hmm.

00:52.286 --> 00:54.455
[sing song voice]
Will.

00:54.555 --> 00:56.290
Can you please come out
to lunch with us?

00:56.390 --> 00:58.159
I can't. Remember?

00:58.259 --> 01:00.261
I'm staring my new job
at the Coalition for Justice.

01:00.361 --> 01:02.663
It's exciting because
I'm gonna get to help people.

01:02.763 --> 01:03.831
Also because
the Coalition for Justice

01:03.931 --> 01:06.634
sounds like the kind of place
where superheroes work.

01:06.734 --> 01:10.304
You know? I'm like
the gay Superman.

01:10.404 --> 01:13.507
Waiting to meet
my Louis Lane.

01:13.607 --> 01:17.278
Jack, can you come
with me?

01:17.378 --> 01:20.648
I would love to join
you and Bobbi for lunch.

01:22.416 --> 01:23.584
I don't know why,

01:23.684 --> 01:26.187
but I'm in the mood
for roast turkey.

01:29.157 --> 01:31.625
And a parade.

01:33.927 --> 01:35.663
It's so great
you're coming.

01:35.763 --> 01:37.198
She loves you.

01:37.298 --> 01:39.667
Of course she's always
been obsessed with gay guys.

01:39.767 --> 01:42.370
It's so sad.

01:42.470 --> 01:45.673
Will, I need
something from you.

01:45.773 --> 01:46.774
I'm sorry, Karen.

01:46.874 --> 01:49.410
I literally peed
two minutes ago.

01:50.678 --> 01:53.614
Not that. I'm trying
to teach my staff

01:53.714 --> 01:54.782
how to spot terrorists.

01:55.749 --> 01:57.785
Could you come by
around 3:00

01:57.885 --> 02:00.688
and dash through
the foyer with a backpack?

02:03.557 --> 02:06.794
Can't. Starting my new job
at the Coalition for Justice.

02:06.894 --> 02:08.796
It's a nonprofit
that helps people

02:08.896 --> 02:10.598
that can't afford lawyers.

02:10.698 --> 02:12.466
Oh. Well, honey,
I'm sorry.

02:12.566 --> 02:14.768
You'll find
a real job soon.

02:14.868 --> 02:17.405
It is a real job.

02:17.505 --> 02:20.274
Right.

02:20.374 --> 02:22.810
And this is
my first liver.

02:25.746 --> 02:29.283
I think what Will's doing
is inspirational.

02:29.383 --> 02:30.684
I don't know why,

02:30.784 --> 02:33.687
but I'm feeling
really thankful today.

02:35.723 --> 02:37.791
[yawning]
Is the game on?

02:39.293 --> 02:42.263
[upbeat jazz music]

02:42.363 --> 02:45.299
