for a change.

04:28.369 --> 04:29.703
What does it matter
where we go, Mom?

04:29.803 --> 04:31.038
You're just gonna order
chicken chow mein

04:32.172 --> 04:33.541
and hot water for the tea bag
that's in your purse.

04:34.675 --> 04:35.976
Oh, well, the tea bag
goes in the place

04:36.009 --> 04:37.345
in my wallet
where the pictures

04:37.445 --> 04:39.580
of the grandchildren
usually go.

04:45.419 --> 04:48.556
Welcome. Here's
your desk right here.

04:48.656 --> 04:50.391
Oh. Mission Control.

04:50.491 --> 04:53.494
[chuckles]
So, put me to work.

04:53.594 --> 04:55.463
I'm ready to fight
for the little people.

04:55.563 --> 04:56.697
Take down some bad guys.

04:56.797 --> 05:00.701
Dole out justice
Truman style.

05:00.801 --> 05:03.971
Okay. I'm gonna go grab
your first case.

05:07.941 --> 05:10.478
Whew. That could've
been embarrassing.

05:10.578 --> 05:12.846
Morning.

05:17.050 --> 05:18.952
Oh, yeah. That desk
only has three legs.

05:19.052 --> 05:21.789
It's fine. That's what
I like about nonprofits.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.391
You know, a little rough
around the edges.

05:23.491 --> 05:26.760
Last work I worked,
all the desks had four legs.

05:26.860 --> 05:29.563
[laughing]
Asses.

05:29.663 --> 05:31.399
Here's the file.

05:31.499 --> 05:34.468
Ah. Ooh. Tenant's rights.

05:34.568 --> 05:37.538
