than one lunch

06:12.706 --> 06:13.841
like that a year.

06:13.941 --> 06:14.975
I know. She's
a nightmare, right?

06:15.075 --> 06:17.077
I'm talking about
you, mister!

06:17.177 --> 06:20.047
What?!
I am appalled

06:20.147 --> 06:21.882
by how you treat her.

06:21.982 --> 06:25.986
That woman is
your mother. Mu-ther!

06:26.086 --> 06:27.555
You are so cruel to her.

06:27.655 --> 06:29.490
Me?! What about her?

06:29.590 --> 06:31.792
Did you not hear
her constant insults?

06:31.892 --> 06:33.160
I may have missed a few.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.028
She's gotta learn
to hold for laughs.

06:35.128 --> 06:37.831
But that's not the point.

06:37.931 --> 06:41.034
You need to treasure
her insults while you can.

06:41.134 --> 06:42.736
Because one day
she'll be gone

06:42.836 --> 06:44.071
and you'll have to hear
how much you suck

06:44.171 --> 06:47.541
from her ghost.

06:47.641 --> 06:49.977
You don't know
anything about it.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.681
Oh, my dear.

06:53.781 --> 06:55.749
No one knows how to be
a good daughter

06:55.849 --> 06:57.117
better than a gay son.

06:58.151 --> 07:01.722
The mother of a gay son

07:01.822 --> 07:05.092
learns to accept him
for who he is.

07:05.192 --> 07:07.628
Except for the sex.

07:12.132 --> 07:15.769
