rarely embark

07:25.045 --> 07:27.981
on this rite of passage.
Thus they are destined

07:28.081 --> 07:30.150
to perpetuate a pattern
of anger and bitchiness.

07:30.250 --> 07:33.854
This would be so much more
clear if I had my slides.

07:35.222 --> 07:37.190
I've seen your slides.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.827
And I don't know
what two Norwegian men

07:39.927 --> 07:42.530
farming naked has to do
with me and my mom.

07:42.630 --> 07:45.198
Grace, if you want
this relationship to change,

07:45.298 --> 07:47.835
you're the one
who has to change it.

07:47.935 --> 07:50.137
Please. Let me help you.

07:50.237 --> 07:54.742
Let me make you
a good gay son.

07:54.842 --> 07:57.010
Except for the sex.

07:57.110 --> 08:01.114
Thanks. But I'll pass.

08:01.214 --> 08:02.015
I'm as gay
as I'd like to be.

08:04.585 --> 08:06.053
This morning when I was
getting dressed

08:06.153 --> 08:10.157
I actually considered
putting a sock in my pants.

08:10.257 --> 08:13.060
Well, you need
something down there.

08:17.665 --> 08:21.569
Jasmine. You have
such beautiful hair.

08:21.669 --> 08:25.038
[chuckles]
I'd like to see it
on my dresser by bedtime.

08:26.640 --> 08:29.009
You know, some people
say "thank you"

08:29.109 --> 08:31.612
when they get a compliment.

08:33.113 --> 08:34.648
I just got another
"help me" note

08:34.748 --> 08:36.049
from one of your maids.

08:36.149 --> 08:39.086
Oh, great. Thanks.

08:42.823 --> 08:46.059
So, I, uh, started
my new job today.

08:46.159 --> 08:48.929
Hmm. That thing where
you save the world

08:49.029 --> 08:51.231
and get paid in soup?
[chuckles]

08:52.299 --> 08:55.202
Doesn't sound like much
of a job to me.

08:56.904 --> 09:00.007
Karen, the work I do
is incredibly important.

09:00.107 --> 09:01.975
I have dedicated my life
to helping those

09:02.075 --> 09:03.944
who cannot help themselves.

09:04.044 --> 09:06.880
You know, since this morning.

09:06.980 --> 09:07.915
And you know,
my first clients,

09:08.015 --> 09:10.083
they live in a rundown
building in Spanish Harlem

09:10.183 --> 09:13.053
that the owner refuses
to bring to code.

09:13.153 --> 09:16.156
Riveting. Why are you here?

09:16.256 --> 09:20.861
Well, because the landlord
is someone we both know.

09:20.961 --> 09:26.166
Oh. I see.

09:26.266 --> 09:30.971
Well, I appreciate
you taking the time

09:31.071 --> 09:33.573
to tell me in person.

09:33.674 --> 09:39.046
So...Marlo Thomas
is a slumlord. Wow.

09:41.248 --> 09:43.016
No, it's not Marlo.

09:43.116 --> 09:44.184
No, no, no!
Let me guess.

09:44.284 --> 09:46.253
It's you, Karen.
I said let me guess.

09:46.353 --> 09:47.688
Is it me?
Yes, it is.

09:47.788 --> 09:50.223
Yay! Woo!

09:52.325 --> 09:54.828
Look, I should be
filing this right now,

09:54.928 --> 09:56.296
but I came down here
to give you a chance

09:56.396 --> 09:58.198
to clear this up
out of court.

09:58.298 --> 09:59.700
I mean the evidence
is overwhelming.

09:59.800 --> 10:00.734
This case is a slam dunk.

10:00.834 --> 10:04.705
Slam dunk!
Shaquille O'Neal!

10:06.173 --> 10:09.242
Okay. I don't know
what that was.

10:09.342 --> 10:11.879
But you have got
to fix this building.

10:11.979 --> 10:13.981
So just sign these papers

10:14.081 --> 10:15.148
agreeing to cover
the costs.

10:15.248 --> 10:16.650
You can make this
whole thing go away.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.887
How do I make
you go away?

10:19.987 --> 10:21.288
You know, years ago

10:21.388 --> 10:23.090
a guy refused
to fix up his building,

10:23.190 --> 10:24.658
and they made him live in.

10:24.758 --> 10:25.726
You know,
and what's worse,

10:25.826 --> 10:26.927
they made a movie
out of it

10:27.027 --> 10:29.162
and they cast Joe Pesci
to play him.

10:29.262 --> 10:30.664
You want Joe Pesci
to play you?

10:30.764 --> 10:32.265
Kiss my A.

10:34.735 --> 10:36.737
I'm sorry.
What did you say

10:36.837 --> 10:40.373
to representative of
Coalition for Justice?

10:40.473 --> 10:42.109
Gosh, I don't know.

10:42.209 --> 10:43.243
Why don't you get
your D out of your ear

10:43.343 --> 10:47.314
and listen to me.

10:47.414 --> 10:49.249
What is the matter
with you?

10:49.349 --> 10:50.784
And why are you
using letters?

10:50.884 --> 10:53.987
Because I'm a lady,
assface.

10:56.990 --> 10:58.792
Okay. That's it.

10:58.892 --> 11:00.360
You've got yourself
a fight.

11:00.460 --> 11:03.831
Take you best shot,
Fairy Mason.

11:06.934 --> 11:09.803
But Karen Walker
is above the law.

11:09.903 --> 11:11.939
You can't touch me!

11:12.039 --> 11:15.175
Oh, oh, oh!

11:15.275 --> 11:17.344
If you go more than 100 feet
from this building,

11:17.444 --> 11:19.112
you will be arrested.

11:19.212 --> 11:21.048
Enjoy your new apartment.

11:30.123 --> 11:36.129
* Raindrops on roses
and whiskers on kittens *

11:36.229 --> 11:37.430
[woman screams]

11:45.105 --> 11:47.207
Hey.

11:47.307 --> 11:49.209
I can't sleep
because I keep thinking

11:49.309 --> 11:52.012
about my relationship
with my mother.

11:52.112 --> 11:56.283
Really? Or is it
because it's only 6:00?

11:56.383 --> 11:57.484
Jack says
I'm horrible to her.

11:57.584 --> 11:59.019
Do you think
I'm horrible to her?

11:59.119 --> 12:01.188
