15:53.753 --> 15:57.057
Those are six bucks
for a dozen at The Whig Easy.

15:57.157 --> 15:59.492
This is an Ava Gabor!

15:59.592 --> 16:02.462
It is irreplaceable!

16:02.562 --> 16:04.131
All right, I am gonna
tell you something

16:04.231 --> 16:07.400
I've heard from my own mother
my whole life.

16:07.500 --> 16:10.470
"Put down that Barbie."

16:10.570 --> 16:15.175
No. You're being an idiot.

16:16.509 --> 16:19.446
So what if she
insults you? Who cares?

16:19.546 --> 16:21.314
The bottom line is
she loves you.

16:21.414 --> 16:23.050
Well, why can't she act
like she does?

16:23.150 --> 16:26.053
She does.
Every day of your life

16:26.153 --> 16:28.621
when she shatters your ego
and makes you feel like nothing

16:28.721 --> 16:32.192
it comes
from a place of love.

16:34.194 --> 16:37.097
Oh, that's sweet.

16:37.197 --> 16:39.532
Twisted, but sweet.

16:41.134 --> 16:43.703
[exhales]

16:45.505 --> 16:46.606
Karen, it's Will.

16:46.706 --> 16:48.475
(Karen)
Go away!

16:48.575 --> 16:50.677
Come on. Open up.

16:50.777 --> 16:52.545
I dropped my rubber gloves
in a puddle of pee

16:52.645 --> 16:55.382
and I can't open doors
with my elbows.

16:55.482 --> 16:57.384
What do you want?
Get in here.

16:57.484 --> 17:00.420
Oh. Well, your timing
could not be worse.

17:00.520 --> 17:01.654
I'm right in the middle
of a game.

17:02.689 --> 17:05.125
Marisol, Concepcion,
this is Will.

17:05.225 --> 17:07.094
The maricon
I told you about.

17:07.194 --> 17:10.097
Oh. Hola, seÃ±or.

17:10.197 --> 17:13.466
She asked if you know
Elton John.

17:14.767 --> 17:18.638
And then she said you look
like a big mincing queen.

17:18.738 --> 17:21.608
Such an efficient language.

17:21.708 --> 17:24.477
Ladies, why don't you
take your cigars

17:24.577 --> 17:27.247
and go up to the roof?

17:27.347 --> 17:28.715
You can touch my mink
one more time

17:28.815 --> 17:31.318
on your way out.
There you go.

17:31.418 --> 17:33.286
Okay. All righty.

17:36.256 --> 17:37.557
Karen, I want to apologize

17:37.657 --> 17:39.459
for putting you
through all this.

17:39.559 --> 17:41.528
What are you
talking about? I'm fine.

17:41.628 --> 17:43.696
I've got everything
I need. A can opener.

17:43.796 --> 17:46.599
A terlet that's not
connected to anything.

17:46.699 --> 17:48.668
And all the lead paint
I can eat.

17:52.472 --> 17:55.608
Look, you don't have to
put on a brave face for me.

17:55.708 --> 17:59.446
Even though I'm sure
it cost you a fortune.

17:59.546 --> 18:01.581
I know that this has
gotta be

18:01.681 --> 18:03.450
a difficult adjustment
for you.

18:03.550 --> 18:06.286
Jorge! Your mother
has been looking for you

18:06.386 --> 18:07.387
for three hours!

18:07.487 --> 18:10.089
Consiga su asno
adentro aqui!

18:13.426 --> 18:15.628
And yet when you
talk to Rosario,

18:15.728 --> 18:18.398
it's, "Scrub-o the tub-o."

18:19.899 --> 18:23.236
The point is...

18:23.336 --> 18:24.537
It's my fault
you're here.

18:24.637 --> 18:27.640
I didn't have to
take it this far.

18:27.740 --> 18:30.543
Then why did you?

18:30.643 --> 18:32.679
I don't know.

18:32.779 --> 18:35.282
I tried to help you,
and then you...

18:35.382 --> 18:37.384
made fun of my job, and I--

18:37.484 --> 18:38.651
You just pushed
my buttons.

18:38.751 --> 18:41.754
Well, isn't this funny?

18:41.854 --> 18:43.756
You know, if anybody
had asked me,

18:43.856 --> 18:47.594
I would've said that
you were pushing my buttons.

18:47.694 --> 18:49.496
Really?
Yes.

18:49.596 --> 18:51.631
I would've written
that check right away

18:51.731 --> 18:54.334
if you hadn't come in
all high and mighty.

18:54.434 --> 18:57.670
Acting all mighty
when I was high.

19:00.707 --> 19:04.677
So we both behaved badly
out of pettiness and spite.

19:04.777 --> 19:07.647
Yeah. And maybe
a little roid rage.

19:12.485 --> 19:15.622
Oh. Honey,
why do we do it?

19:15.722 --> 19:17.490
Why are we always
at each other?

19:17.590 --> 19:20.693
[chuckles]
Can you imagine
what Nora Ephron

19:20.793 --> 19:23.363
would do
with our story?

19:23.463 --> 19:26.833
No. Although I'm sure
it would feel familiar.

19:26.933 --> 19:31.271
And we could sleep
through most of it.

19:31.371 --> 19:32.839
Look, I'm gonna
make a call.

19:32.939 --> 19:33.873
I'm gonna get you
out of this.

19:33.973 --> 19:35.542
No, no, no, honey.
That's okay.

19:35.642 --> 19:38.411
I'll finish out my week.
It'll be good for me.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.547
Anyway,
thanks for stopping by.

19:40.647 --> 19:43.350
I'm gonna run up to the roof
and meet the girls.

19:43.450 --> 19:44.684
Mind if I keep you
company for a bit?

19:44.784 --> 19:46.553
Well, no. I'd like that.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.488
But, you know, just to be
on the safe side,

19:48.588 --> 19:51.190
let's talk real loudly
about how your dad's black.

19:55.995 --> 19:59.432
How's the chow mein?
Do you want some more?

19:59.532 --> 20:05.338
I was just distracted
by your garish eye shadow.

20:05.438 --> 20:08.207
Do you really need
three colors?

20:08.308 --> 20:10.343
Mom, this is not
garish. It--

20:16.716 --> 20:19.652
Why are you smiling?

20:19.752 --> 20:23.823
Are my boobs
under my arms again?

20:26.793 --> 20:30.763
No, Mom.
Well, yes, but--

20:30.863 --> 20:35.001
No, I'm--

20:36.469 --> 20:39.606
I'm smiling because...

20:39.706 --> 20:41.874
whatever you say to me,
I know you love me.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.611
Well, of course I do,
darling. I adore you.

20:44.711 --> 20:46.913
That's what I thought.

20:47.013 --> 20:48.815
It's just like
when you say

20:48.915 --> 20:51.851
I'm too old
to play Juliet,

20:51.951 --> 20:55.888
I know it's just your way
of saying you love me.

20:59.526 --> 21:02.729
Yeah, that's exactly
what I mean.

21:02.829 --> 21:05.865
You're so sweet.
I love you.

21:05.965 --> 21:07.734
Ow.
Oh. Ow.

21:07.834 --> 21:09.001
Oh, I found the other one.

